cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

The paper discusses a technique for interpreting non-linear dimensionality reduction methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of automatic differentiation suggests a focus on optimization and numerical methods, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
